<title>UK: Bass up after UK blocks Carlsberg merger.</title>
<headline>Bass up after UK blocks Carlsberg merger.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Bass Plc rose 24p to 759p on Friday after news that Britain's government had blocked the prosposed acquisition of Carlsberg-Tetley A/S.  </p>
<p>&quot;Carlsberg is not a great performer and people are saying it is a good thing Bass are out of it,&quot; said one dealer.</p>
<p>Uncertainty over the decision from the UK's Monopolies and Mergers Commission, MMC, has dogged the shares recently, dealers said.</p>
<p>The MMC said it was also seeking an undertaking that Bass will divest its 50 percent stake in Carlsberg-Tetley.</p>
<p>The news also benefited Scottish &amp; Newcastle, which now remains Britain's largest brewer. S&amp;N which rose this morning on hopes of robust results on Monday, extended its gains, rising 6-1/2p to 635-1/2p.</p>
